When you talk about a person's abs, you always hear about a 6-pack.&nbsp;

&nbsp;_|_&nbsp; 
&nbsp;_|_
&nbsp;&nbsp; |

My friend in this story had a five pack. 5 not 6. It wasn't even 2 across that were stuck together. They were up and down.

&nbsp;_|_&nbsp; 
&nbsp;_|
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|

&nbsp;So we had a basement escapade last night. Completely pointless and childish, but oh so much fun. Every once in a while it's necessary&nbsp;to play pointless children's games.&nbsp;Kayte and&nbsp;Adam&nbsp;knocked at the basement window and asked &quot;Who's in the basement?&quot;&nbsp; 

Tyrone answered with &quot;Who do you think?&quot;&nbsp; 
Kayte and&nbsp;Adam &quot;We'll be right down.&quot;&nbsp; 
Tyrone &quot;No one will be here.&quot;&nbsp; 

And then we all grabbed our stuff and ran, literally ran, out the door, down the hall, and up the stairs to the third floor with&nbsp;my friend &nbsp;yelling over his shoulder &quot;Someone grab my shoes.&quot;
